    public class AccumulatorCompleteRange<A>

    • Constructor Detail

      • AccumulatorCompleteRange

        public AccumulatorCompleteRange(ChunkedList<?> toAllocate,
                                Function<Long,A> initFunc)
        Constructor. Allocates every ThreadLocalAccumulator with an individual accumulator for every index contained in the ranges contained by the ChunkedList given as parameter.

        Note that subsequent addition of ranges to the ChunkedList will not be reflected into the instance created by calling this constructor. If the ranges contained by a ChunkedList change and this change needs to be reflected by the AccumulatorCompleteRange, a new instance should be created.

        Parameters:
        toAllocate - ChunkedList whose contained ranges will be allocated for thread-local accumulators prepared by this instance
        initFunc - the function used to allocate the individual allocators

      • AccumulatorCompleteRange

        public AccumulatorCompleteRange(Collection<LongRange> ranges,
                                Function<Long,A> initFunc)
        Constructor. Allocates every ThreadLocalAccumulator with an individual accumulator for every index contained in the ranges given as parameter.

        It is assumed that the ranges given as parameter are mutually exclusive. In other words, no two ranges should overlap. Otherwise, exceptions will be thrown when using this accumulator.

        Also, subsequent modifications to the collection given as parameter will not influence the behavior of previously created AccumulatorCompleteRange instance. If a AccumulatorCompleteRange is desired on a different set of ranges, a new instance should be created.

        Parameters:
        ranges - the ranges on which this accumulator will be capable of accumulating values

    • Method Detail

      • newThreadLocalAccumulator

        protected Accumulator.ThreadLocalAccumulator<A> newThreadLocalAccumulator()
        Description copied from class: Accumulator
        Factory method which creates a new ThreadLocalAccumulator for an upcoming thread to use to accumulate information.

        This method is for internal use only. It is used when there are not enough thread-local accumulators for the level of parallelism desired. Each Accumulator implementation should implement this method to return a Accumulator.ThreadLocalAccumulator instance fitted with its appropriate accumulator allocation policy.

        Specified by:

        a newly created
